author: {'nr_reviews': 0, 'age_group': '', 'city': '', 'type': 'solo_traveller', 'user_id': 100339818, 'countrycode': 'au', 'name': 'Sura', 'helpful_vote_count': 0, 'type_string': 'Solo traveller'}
title: Perfect location, clean, quiet, great staff, I would definitely return.

cons: It’s an older style hotel that has been renovated so only 3 lifts that can get overcrowded. However staff were quick to let us use the service lift. Also - the ‘extras’ advertised on booking.com need updating as the discounts to Iolani palace and bishop museum were not an actual thing. Room service food was awesome but one night the ordering app did not work (using apps for ordering would be tricky for my elderly parents for still travel).
pros: The location was he best in Waikiki as it’s at the end of the strip, I booked a room facing diamond head so I woke up to greenery every morning (also park and zoo across the road). As soon as you walk out of the hotel turn right and there is the beach. The open air lobby with beautifully styled local history has you feeling on vacation immediately. Free yoga 3 mornings was excellent. Free beach chairs towels and sunscreen on offer from friendly staff and concierge very helpful.

author: {'nr_reviews': 0, 'age_group': '', 'city': '', 'type': 'solo_traveller', 'countrycode': 'us', 'name': 'Matt', 'helpful_vote_count': 0, 'type_string': 'Solo traveller', 'user_id': 71693343, 'avatar': 'https://graph.facebook.com/v2.9/10153296789591942/picture?type=square&height=64&width=64'}
title: The Queen is fit for a queen!

pros: Queen Kapiolani is perfectly located on the 'edge' of Waikiki.  If you walk one way, you can be in the midst of al the action and energy.  But, if you walk the other way, there is the tranquility of Queen Kapiolani Park with its incredible views of Diamond Head.  The hotel itself is beautiful and the corner rooms have views of both Diamond Head and the sunset.  The front desk staff are courteous, knowledgable and friendly.

pros: this is a lovely, recently renovated historic hotel just off the main Waikiki strip. Open-air lobby, excellent coffee shop, great food and snacks. Beach towels available (for free). Really good location. Friendly helpful staff. Bed was comfortable, room was clean. Would stay again!

author: {'countrycode': 'au', 'avatar': 'https://graph.facebook.com/v2.9/10208513830181171/picture?type=square&height=64&width=64', 'nr_reviews': 0, 'name': 'Cettina', 'type': 'solo_traveller', 'city': '', 'user_id': 132528488, 'age_group': '', 'helpful_vote_count': 0, 'type_string': 'Solo traveller'}
title: Pleasant

cons: The bathroom in my dorm could use a good scrub of toilet area due to male urine spray. Or maybe train all guys to sit for urinating, Lol. My old bones would have appreciated a memory foam mattress, but the innerspring mattress was definitely better than some mattresses I've slept on.
pros: Loved the two minute walk to beach front! Lots of beach items to borrow was a big money saver for me. Chair, beach mat, boogie board, umbrella and snorkel equipment were all available! The communal area has plenty of tables and seating, There are four roomy hammocks to relax in. There are 4 full size fridges for food storage. And a large shelf system to store your dry goods. Just remember to label everything, it makes it easier for staff when they clean and for you to track what you have or need to get  I was proactive in keeping my supplies collected in a bag in fridge, freezer and on dry shelf, it made it easy to track supplies and plan my menu's. I highly recommend shopping and cooking there at the hostel when staying and on a tight budget! The kitchen is well stocked with cookware, utensils and dinnerware. It is a small cooking space, so getting to know the use flow of the kitchen helps give everyone a chance to prep and cook. There is no real available counter space for prepping, but plenty of cutting boards and knives to take to one of the tables for prep work. Be a team worker and wash, dry and put away everything you use, pretend momma is watching, Lol.

author: {'type': 'review_category_group_of_friends', 'nr_reviews': 0, 'name': 'Kate', 'countrycode': 'au', 'helpful_vote_count': 1, 'city': '', 'user_id': 30351474, 'type_string': 'Group of friends', 'age_group': ''}
title: Exceptional

cons:
Rooms (I stayed in two different rooms during my stay, my first room was next to elevator and I could hear the elevator moving in its shaft whenever it was used, so after 3 nights they were finally able to move me to another room) were rather outdated, dilapidating paint on the doors, scratches, etc). The hotel is extremely busy with lots of shops inside, farmers market twice a week, it gives a Las Vegas feel. The swimming pool is very small for a hotel that size (the hotel combines two 40-story towers).
At check-in I was asked if I preferred my room cleaned in the morning or afternoon, I said I did t have a preference so they put me down for the afternoon house keeping. However, during my 8 night stay my room was cleaned only once and I had to request it at reception.
pros:
Location. 
The staff were kind and accommodating, willing to help.

title: Great value for money

cons: Parking lots are small and tight, hard to find a spot if you return to the hotel late. Although the hotel advertised for free continental breakfast, it was mis-advertised and not even close to what we expected. Unless you pay and order the real(?) breakfast, you will get a mini breakfast (muffins and boiled egg, fruit...etc) in the takeout container. Restaurant workers were rude and impolite. We utilized McDonald's near the hotel during our stay instead.
pros: It's a bit old but clean and reasonably great value. Staffs are very friendly and kind. The location of the hotel is fantastic and only a minute walk from the Waikiki beachfront and everything. We stayed in a corner deluxe studio and the rooms are spacious and have great amenities including a kitchenette and oceanview. We may stay here again!

title: Pleasant

cons: I didn't like the additional fee of $35 day for Grab & Go breakfast & beach towels. I felt the grab & go breakfast needs improvement... not worth the value for a hard boiled egg and muffin. In addition, the Hotel is quite outdated and could use a much needed room & pool renovation.
pros: Waikiki Hotel Resort is located in the heart of Waikiki Beach. Just steps away from restaurants and ABC gift shops. Across  the street is Life Guard Tower 2C... a great calm beach for the family. The staff provided warm and friendly check-in service. This fantastic location is within walking distance from just about all restaurants & the nightlife bars. It's not necessary to rent a car unless you schedule water activates in the North Shore.

title: this was our first time in Waikiki and this was a nice boutique hotel .Quiet . If you’re not into big resorts I recommen

cons:
- No laundry.
- Needs more precaution signage at rooftop/pool area. (“Watch Your Step”, “Steep Stairs”, etc). There are “blind spots” where one can easily miss a step and/or slip. 
- Lobby (and also inside the elevators) has an intense floral scent, very very strong. I always felt nauseated walking in the lobby, so I would often hurriedly walk by fast to avoid the overall strong floral scent. 
- Ramp for luggage, baby strollers, wheelchairs. 
- For the room I specially stayed in: 
  - Bedside lamp not functioning properly.
  - Outlet on bedside table not functioning.
  - Shower-head pressure was weak.
  - Curtain was missing it’s “rod” to move the curtains.
pros:
- Surrounded by numerous and various shops.
- Walking distance to Waikiki Beach, restaurants, etc.
- Location was perfect in my opinion.
- Hotel interior and style—-very vibrant!

title: 48hrs in Honolulu

cons: The room was a lot smaller than expected. The washroom was a little outdated and rundown but still functional. The view wasn't the greatest as a lot of buildings blocked the view of the ocean.
pros: The beach access was very accessible. There were tons of food options in the immediate surrounding area and also a lot of shopping. The Shoreline staff were amazing! Check in and check out was quick and simple.

author: {'user_id': 102960802, 'helpful_vote_count': 0, 'nr_reviews': 0, 'age_group': '', 'city': '', 'name': 'William', 'type': 'solo_traveller', 'countrycode': 'us', 'type_string': 'Solo traveller'}
title: very nice hotel, will definitely come back again.

cons: The Infinity pool was shallow and surrounded by tall buildings so sometimes the sun was limited  and it got a little overcast and breezy . The hot tub was a great addition though. There was no balcony to sit and enjoy the view from the mountain view  room , there was only  enough space to stand . There were no night gowns, but not a big deal.
pros:
Unlike the typical  chain hotels, check in was fast without a huge influx of hotel guests at the same time and the lifts were super fast . The location was excellent surrounded by shops , eateries and few mins walk from beach . All staff at reception and housekeeping were friendly  and helpful .
I suggest the use of a microwave in the hotel would be a big plus.  . There was a laundrette ( wash and dry)  on the 8th floor which took coins which was useful (around 10 dollars worth)  , but the coins sometimes got stuck and it would have been better to just purchase a token from reception . Filtered  water machines are available 24/7 in the lobby and pool area and the hotel provides water flasks which was a nice touch. The electric loo, sprinklers and blinds were supercool . 
The mountain view room on 23rd floor was spacious, with a spectacular view through the super sized windows  especially delightful at night time . Coffee facilities were great and I had a kettle for tea making.
I would definitely consider returning to the hotel esp as they are covid considerate and have individually sealed items items like cups , toiletries and remote .

pros: The location of the hotel was great as it was away from the crowds of Waikiki. The locals use the park across the street and by the beach. If you’re up for it, you can walk to the top of Diamond Head and back from the hotel. (But not with sandals.) Cut across the park and don’t follow Google maps. Hotel staff were super kind and helpful. My corner sea and mountain view room was perfect. Thank you!

author: {'user_id': 37704987, 'helpful_vote_count': 0, 'city': '', 'nr_reviews': 0, 'age_group': '', 'name': 'Farshid', 'countrycode': 'us', 'type_string': 'Solo traveller', 'type': 'solo_traveller'}

cons: Although there really is no spectacular view possible from the property, it still would have been nice to have a more comfortable balcony, perhaps with a lounge chair in addition to the small chairs and table.
pros: The room was very clean and comfortable. The robe and slippers are a nice touch and the toiletries are top-notch quality.
title: Very peaceful and positive experience.

cons: Nothing really.
pros: My 9th Floor corner room had 2 beds, 2 patios and 2 views, one of Diamond Head and the lush green valleys behind it.   The other view looked out over the sparkling blue ocean, amongst the other high rise buildings in the Diamond Head area.   Beach towels are available and you can wander to several small beaches nearby.   There's a small convenience store in the next building, and 3 fine-dining restaurants steps away.   I loved the park and the seclusion from Waikiki, yet just a walk away.   A great place to stay.

title: Great and beautiful!!

cons: Being located right on Ala Moana Boulevard, which is a major thoroughfare in Waikiki, the noise from the traffic can get pretty loud if your room is near the road. I was able to get my room switched to a quieter side of the building, thanks to Lincoln, and that alleviated the problem.
pros: The location was supreme. I was there for a conference that had events at both the Hawaii Convention Center and the Hilton Hawaiian Village, and this hotel was within easy walking distance of either venue. Also close by are a bus station, an ABC store (a convenience store that opens early and closes late), and many restaurants as well as the gigantic Ala Moana Center shopping mall. The staff, and especially Lincoln (at the front desk), were super welcoming and efficient in addressing any requests that I had.

title: Pleasant

cons: The room I got overlooked Kalakaua and was pretty noisy until after 1.30am so if you're there on the weekend (I was there Friday night) expect a fair amount of noise from drunk tourists outside if you're on the street side of the building. I expect other rooms were quieter so perhaps ask for a room on the pool side of the building. Had it not been for the noise (which in all fairness is largely out of the control of the hotel), I'd have scored the property higher.
pros: Polynesian Residences is well located for Waikiki, right on Kalakaua Ave, towards the north end of Waikiki. The room I got was a deluxe double which was pretty big, comfortable and very clean. The price for Waikiki was fantastic and half the price of other hotels in the area.

author: {'user_id': 81210155, 'helpful_vote_count': 2, 'age_group': '', 'type_string': 'Group of friends', 'type': 'review_category_group_of_friends', 'countrycode': 'au', 'nr_reviews': 0, 'name': 'Amanda', 'city': ''}
title: Pleasant

cons: The family suite didn't have any couches or dining tables, only the beds and a small desk. No type of breakfast included at the hotel.
pros: Check in and check out were really easy and fast. Good location on the main strip. ABC stores and restaurants all nearby. A couple blocks away from the beach, easy to walk to. The staff were nice and friendly. Anytime we needed anything they were quick to respond. Free beach towels and beach chairs to borrow. Rooms and beds comfortable enough to sleep in at the end of the day.
author: {'helpful_vote_count': 2, 'user_id': 344790234, 'age_group': '', 'type_string': 'Group of friends', 'type': 'review_category_group_of_friends', 'name': 'Chris', 'city': '', 'nr_reviews': 0, 'countrycode': 'us'}
title: Great for a group of young adults

cons:
I didn’t realise that there wasn’t a kitchen/dining room in the hotel, also the minibar wasn’t stocked (and couldn’t be), but it was a great fridge for our own bottles of water etc. 
also, it was USD $4 for a bottle of water on the table in the hotel room - I just thought a place as hot as Waikiki/Honolulu, you’d get a bottle a water included in the room rate each night.  But they did give you a 300ml bottle of water at check-in, which was nice. 
The rooms had a small Kitchenette (microwave and bench space with a coffee machine) but I didn’t see any cutlery, or glassware.  There were two glasses in the bathroom, but no wine glasses in the room if you brought a bottle of wine back to enjoy the evening in your balcony.
pros:
Polynesian Residences is lovely, it’s clean, modern and really comfortable. 
The staff were very friendly and welcoming, I was able to pre-pay for the whole stay before arriving (inclusive of the hotel fees and local taxes - because I don’t love dealing with the bill upon checking out, as I had to be in a taxi at 5:30am for my departing flight Ha-Ha). 
There was a nice pool out the back, that had daily morning Yoga. 
The hotel was well positioned on the Waikiki strip, next to Hard Rock Cafe, and opposite an ABC Store (convenience store) and only a short walk to the beach.
title: Great holiday, lovely hotel

cons: Parking is expensive and it is taxed for a garage tax when the cars are parked on the lot in front of the hotel.
pros: The marketing is very deceptive when booking your stay here when it comes to Ocean Views. A premium Ocean View sounds like the best room they would have but it is not. You have to stand on the balcony and look around the corner to view the Ocean. The best room here is an Ocean Front room which was deceptive online and not explained. When I mentioned to the resort, they said they can switch our room but only for the last night of our stay because they were all rented out. Also, the fact the hotel has no room service available was not good.

author: {'age_group': '', 'nr_reviews': 0, 'type_string': 'Solo traveller', 'name': 'Sahar', 'user_id': 1101077, 'city': '', 'type': 'solo_traveller', 'countrycode': 'us', 'helpful_vote_count': 0}
title: Passable

cons: Too much to list, upon check in we went to our room, unpacked, and I went downstairs for some bottled water to keep in the mini fridge. I opened the mini fridge and there were someone else’s  left overs in the fridge... I went downstairs with those Togo containers put on the front desk and they assured me it wouldn’t happen again (how is it supposed to happen again if it’s the room we are staying in). The next day we had left early and we’re gone for a majority of the day, we came back and the bed wasn’t made, towels still on the floor, garbage in cans, I had to call the front desk and inform them of this, we left for I late dinner and came back and was taken care of finally. The third day I was enjoying my coffee on the balcony trying to enjoy my coffee, but there was a distinct smell of weed in the air. I looked over the edge and here was a homeless man sitting on a rock in the bushes smoking weed, he also had a large knife with him that he wrapped and unwrapped in a shirt a few times. I called the front desk, they had security ask him to move, he left for about 20-25 minutes, then came back to the same area. I called again, security asked him to leave again, hotel manager called our room to get an accurate description of the guy. The following day he was back again, but I was to the point I didn’t care any more, and I’m assuming the security had the same feelings. The room we were placed in was right next to and behind the elevator, so all day and night that is all we heard... I would not recommend this property
pros: I liked that the AC in the room would get to the desired temp quickly

author: {'type_string': 'Solo traveller', 'user_id': 126305495, 'age_group': '', 'countrycode': 'au', 'type': 'solo_traveller', 'nr_reviews': 0, 'name': 'Lee', 'helpful_vote_count': 0, 'city': ''}
title: Exceptional

cons:
The staff at this place: a) did not tell us anything about the facilities or rooms or check outs or valet or ANYTHING when we checked in - just validated us by ID and then gave us keys.
b) the pool was tiny and I thought I was at my home pool and had invited too many people over as it was crowded and then I heard from another guest that some people from another accommodation had been told to come to ours which may have explained the amount of people but does not explain why such an expensive accommodation has such a small pool area = not relaxing with everyone on top of each other and needing seating....
c) communications were terrible again upon checkout - could not/ would not explain a very significant daily tax charge, basics like how is this calculated? why was it so much greater than the 2 other Waikiki accommodations'/ resorts we stayed at during the same vacation period?
We just did not think this was anywhere near value for money as the service was poor (with the exclusion of the housekeeping and valet staff), the facilities were not any better in any way if at all, to the other 2 less expensive resorts we stayed at and they really lacked any customer service skills/ pleasantries/ ability to answer queries/
pros: Good location and the rooms were clean.  The nearby beach was lovely although very crowded at the time we visited - nothing to do with the hotel.
